Foreign direct investment in  Kenya 
dropped 38 percent to 14 billion shillings ($154.7 million) in
the three months to June from a year earlier, Business Daily
reported, citing the Kenya Investment Authority.  The trend may continue this year amid political uncertainty
ahead of next yearâ€™s presidential election, the Nairobi-based
